<dl id="n35211a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35211a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35211a"> 211(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> unguent ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ibn Jubair <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> in the 12th century describes the mart of Mecca in the eight days following the feast as full of gems, unguents, precious drugs, and all rare merchandise from India, Irak, Khorasan, and every part of the Moslem world. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 951</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
